Finally trying out the @armanibeauty Luminous Silk Foundation and It’s worth the hype. Now I need to get the perfect shade match to seal the deal.  The foundation has an exclusive formula with micro-fil Technology that allows the pigment to lay flat on the skin which is responsible for this second skin effect. 

Now does it give me a satin finish? It absolutely does and wears well throughout the day. 
#armanibeauty #armaniluminoussilk #foundation #flawlessmakeup

Have you guys tried this and how did you like it?

It’s Leo season and we celebrated Simba’s birthday last night with a dinner with friends. His actual birthday is days away but an early celebration never hurt no body. 
Please join me in wishing him a happy birthday ❤️

As we grow older we are always thinking, “it’s too late to do this or that.” But the actual truth is that it’s only in your head and no one actually cares what you decide to do at whatever age you are and that some one out there is actually waiting for someone like you to take a bold step and do what’s right for you so they can be inspired and follow suit. 

These are thoughts that I am currently having and happy to see where they take me. Have you made a big pivot in your life? How did you do it and what pushed you to do it?

Love receiving PR from brands that I am already in love with like @lancomeofficial who have been consistent in developing inclusive products for the longest time. They are intentional with what they share on the market after doing lots of research on all skin types. 

I got introduced to this brand when I started my skincare journey and one of my favourite products was their Bienfait Multi-Vital which was discontinued. Since then I have been a staunch Lancome die hard and two years back I started using their Renergie Triple serum which Is a 3 in one serum with Hyaluronic acid, VitaminC, Niacinamide and Ferluoiv Acid. All this gives you a powerful anti aging concentrate.

Can’t believe I am on their PR list and I also have a campaign with them coming out this fall. So can’t wait to share more on that.

If you are looking to start an anti-aging beauty routine I recommend trying out this powerful serum and Renergie HPN cream.

#lancome #renergietripleserum #HPN #skincare #skin #canadianinfluencer #vancouverinfluencer #flawlessskin

I think the new skincare trend will be seeing beauty brands come up with more skin barrier restoration products. When Rhode first came out, I really thought…not another celebrity skincare brand. But I took time to actually inform myself about their 3 skin products and the ingredients involved. 

I was wrong. I feel like they are really intentional on the strategy they are taking when it comes to what the skin actually needs and I hope they continue on this path. 

What do you guys think about skin Barrier restoration and how many times are you including a product like this in your routine? Is it part of your skin cycling?

Things I have added to my body routine that I am now obsessed with.

1. This @larocheposay cleanser oil does the job but above all I love it’s “baby like” smell. Gives me a little smile when I use it. It’s like a memory of my childhood. Also I highly recommend this if you have sensitive skin.

2. This is the @aesopskincare exfoliating redemption body scrub. I know it says use 2/3 times a week but I swear the days I miss using it I feel like I have not pampered myself enough. It smells so good and the scrub is gentle and feels like I am in my own spa.

What’s new in your shower routine that I should probably try?

🌟 Still on the Week’s Theme @the_shecentre_podcast: AUTHENTICITY 🌟

In this video clip, we discuss the challenges faced by influencers. It’s evident that many Africans living abroad miss out on opportunities because of their accents. 🗣️🌍

For some reason, many companies prioritize assimilation over knowledge or expertise. They expect immigrants to shed their identities and pretend to be something they’re not just to be considered for marketing or influencing roles. This extends to appearance too. Models and influencers have spoken out about discrimination based on color, hair texture, and more. 🚫

It’s baffling that this still occurs in a digital and interconnected world. Like Viccy said, you can’t please everyone in every space. There will always be something they criticize. 🎯

So, promote your authentic brand identity and the right companies or individuals will align with you. Focus on being your best, but never change who you are to please anyone. 🙌

Discover more about Viccy’s journey and how she stays true to herself by clicking the link in my bio. 🎧📌

#podcastersofinstagram #podcast #contentcreation #canadiancontentcreator #vancouvercontentcreator 
#AuthenticityMatters #InfluencerChallenges #BeYourself  #StayTrue #SheCentrePodcast 🎤🌼

Tested out the @guerlain PARURE Gold skin foundation and loved the finish. 

SHADE MATCH
I picked out shade 8N but realized that it was a bit red-ish for me so I may have to get the shade below this for a perfect match. Not so many shades for dark skin but there are few choices.

FINISH
The foundation feels really velvety and rich. Has a matte finish but also has a healthy glow. It wears nicely throughout the day as it’s a long wear foundation. 

BENEFITS 
It is a skincare based foundation and so this means you are treating your skin the entire day you are wearing it with extra hydration, skin barrier strengthening and anti-aging. 

#guerlain #luxurymakeup #luxuryskincare #guerlainmakeup #guerlainparuregold #skin #foundation #vancouverbeautyblogger #canadianbeautyblogger #skincaretips

I started this work week with so much anxiety because of my hair. I had taken out my braids over the weekend and there was a gap between then and my next braiding appointment. 

It felt like my natural hair was on full display, untamed and wild, and I wasn’t sure how I was going to show up to office or to handle the public stares.

This year marks my first journey embracing my natural black hair, and let me tell you, the struggle is real. From figuring out how to make it ‘presentable’ to questioning if I should wear it more often at work, it’s been a journey of self-discovery.

I got to the office so sad and down and decided to have a discussion with my boss at work about the anxiety, and her kindness struck a chord. She asked, ‘Would wearing your natural hair more often ease the anxiety?’ It got me thinking – is the anxiety rooted in not embracing my natural beauty openly and frequently?

So here I am, sharing the raw, real journey of being a black woman with natural hair. It’s about self-discovery, breaking free from norms, and asking the tough questions. Because what’s the point of this journey if I don’t embrace and flaunt my natural crown? It’s still a journey…am not any where close to fully embracing my natural hair.

Cheers to the natural hair journey, the ups, the downs, and the courage to show up authentically. #NaturalHairJourney #Authenticity
